Privacy Policy for MindRush
Last Updated: February 12, 2026

TLL Developers ("we," "our," or "us") is committed to protecting your privacy. This Privacy Policy explains how your personal information is collected, used, and disclosed by MindRush (the "App").

This Privacy Policy applies to our website, and its associated subdomains (collectively, our "Service") alongside our application, MindRush. By accessing or using our Service, you signify that you have read, understood, and agree to our collection, storage, use, and disclosure of your personal information as described in this Privacy Policy and our Terms of Service.

1. Information We Collect
We collect information to provide better services to all our users. The information we collect depends on how you use our App.

A. Information You Provide to Us
Account Data: When you launch the App, we use Firebase Anonymous Authentication to create a temporary account. This assigns you a unique User ID (uid) to store your progress. You do not need to provide a name, email, or phone number to play.

Game Data: We store your game progress, including high scores, daily streaks, puzzle completion times, and challenge history in our databases (Cloud Firestore).

B. Information Collected Automatically
Device Information: We collect information about the device you use to access the App, such as the hardware model, operating system version, and unique device identifiers.

Usage Data: We use Firebase Analytics to collect data on how you interact with the App, such as which puzzles you play most, session duration, and crash reports.

Advertising Data: We use Google AdMob to display advertisements. AdMob may collect and use your device's Advertising ID (AAID) to serve personalized or non-personalized ads.

2. How We Use Your Information
We use the information we collect for the following purposes:

To Provide the Service: To track your daily streaks, save your progress (Scores, Challenges), and maintain your position on the Leaderboards.

To Improve the App: Analyzing usage trends (via Firebase Analytics) helps us balance puzzle difficulty (Flip Grid, Queens, etc.) and fix bugs.

To Send Notifications: We use Firebase Cloud Messaging to send you reminders about the Daily Challenge or streak alerts. You can opt-out of these in your device settings.

To Show Advertisements: To keep MindRush free, we display Banner, Interstitial, and Rewarded ads via AdMob.

3. Third-Party Services and SDKs
We share information with third-party vendors who provide services on our behalf. These partners have their own privacy policies:

Google Firebase (Analytics, Auth, Firestore, Crashlytics, Messaging): Used for backend services, authentication, and data analysis.

